external_knowledge:
- 'captains' is an allegorical term for employees with the role of 'Manager';
- 'steer the ship' metaphorically means leading a department;
- 'have not yet left the voyage' implies that the employment status is 'Active'.

- "seeds planted in the fertile ground of the company" refers to the employees starting their career at the organization;
- "complete identities" represents the full names of the employees (first, middle, and last);
- "gardens (departments) they nurture" symbolizes the departments the employees belong to;
- "keys (access levels) they carry to unlock the gates of knowledge" represents the access levels of the employees in the company.

Swimming above the tide: refers to performing better than average;
Shining brighter: indicates earning more than the average salary;
Peers: employees within the same department.
